                            <comment id="141906" author="standan" created="Wed, 10 Feb 2016 23:14:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another instance found for Full tag 2.7.66 -EL7.1 Server/SLES11 SP3 Client, build# 3314&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/94600ac4-ca7b-11e5-9609-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/94600ac4-ca7b-11e5-9609-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another instance found for Full tag 2.7.66 -EL6.7 Server/SLES11 SP3 Client, build# 3316&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/d79e551e-cce9-11e5-8b0e-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/d79e551e-cce9-11e5-8b0e-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="141082" author="bogl" created="Wed, 3 Feb 2016 23:27:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the initial comment from 09/Oct/15 is still true.  tar in sles11 versions doesn&apos;t know those options.  not a regression, has always been so.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="141080" author="standan" created="Wed, 3 Feb 2016 23:24:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another failure for master : Tag 2.7.66 FULL - EL7.1 Server/SLES11 SP3 Client, build# 3314&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/94600ac4-ca7b-11e5-9609-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/94600ac4-ca7b-11e5-9609-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is issue has occurred around 34 times in past 30 days.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="136267" author="sarah" created="Mon, 14 Dec 2015 22:37:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;same error on master/3264 &lt;br/&gt;
server: RHEL6.7&lt;br/&gt;
client: SLES11 SP3&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/4488bc06-a052-11e5-a33d-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/4488bc06-a052-11e5-a33d-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="136080" author="standan" created="Fri, 11 Dec 2015 18:53:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;master, build# 3264, 2.7.64 tag&lt;br/&gt;
Regression:EL7.1 Server/SLES11 SP3 Client&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/015d4b86-9f2b-11e5-bf9b-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/015d4b86-9f2b-11e5-bf9b-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="130018" author="bogl" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2015 22:18:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this a regression, I believe it&apos;s always been this way.  As far as I can tell the --xattrs, --no-xattrs options aren&apos;t known to the tar versions native on sles11sp3 and sles11sp4.  They never have been.  fwiw, the newer tar version native on sles12 does know these options.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
